#!/usr/bin/env groovy

// With the ability to defer arguments' type verification to runtime
// polymorphism in Groovy is on steroids.


// compile-type type-chicking
// (Java) 부자연스럽고
// 점점 그 중요성이 감소하고 있다.

// the static type-checking amounts to mere annoyance and lowers our producitivity.


// Dynamic Typing
// - We let the language figure out the type based on the context.
// - a greater degree of polymorphism
// - less casting


// Dynamic Typing != Weak Typing
// If we listen closely we may hear the compiler laugh for
// our reliance on the type safety it pretends to provide.
// This is an example of static typing with weak typing at runtime.




